n Capital-The Real Data to Watch -- tChapter 18: Aristotle, Infrastructure, and Capital -- tPart 6: Tonight the Role of Government Will Be Played By... -- tChapter 19: Government's Role: Past and Future -- tChapter 20: Government's Job -- tChapter 21: Funding the Government: Taxes and Debt-Good, Bad, and Completely Lost -- tChapter 22: Expense Management and the Government- A Misnomer? -- tChapter 23: More Gray and Purple, Less Gridlock -- tPart 7: Business is Different Now, But It Always Is -- tChapter 24: Business Structures-Think Again -- tChapter 25: Business Investment-What People Watch and Should Watch -- tChapter 26: Business Cycle Theory: It's Wrong and Slow -- tChapter 27: Tearing Down and Running Around the Barriers to Entry -- tChapter 28: Incumbents Can Fight Back -- tChapter 29: Food and Energy -- tChapter 30: Supply Chains, Outsourcing, and Innovation -- tChapter 31: Measure of Trade -- tChapter 32: The Invisible Consumer: Customer Retention, Big Data, and Customer Service -- tPart 8: Value, Volatility, Uncertainty-Different Arrangement but the Song Remains the Same -- tChapter 33: Value -- tChapter 34: Volatility and Risk Measures-A Point of View -- tChapter 35: Uncertainty-The Opportunity -- tPart 9: Random Ramble and Concluding Topics -- tChapter 36: New Industries and What to Do about Them -- tChapter 37: Emerging Economies-New Paths -- tChapter 38: Socially Responsible Investing and Environmental, Social, and Governance Factors -- tChapter 39: Trends, Data, Correlations, and a Few Other Things-Again -- tChapter 40: Never Close Your Eyes or You Will Miss Something -- tIndex  aEconomic measures and concepts like GDP, inflation, business cycles and supply chains that were created decades ago are being disrupted and altered by technology. These changes affect asset values, interest rates, stock valuations, barriers to entry, as well as regression and correlation analysis. That Doesn't Work Anymore discusses how to adapt traditional data to these changes and outlines ways to use newer and better tools that help you make good investment and business decisions. The book's short pragmatic chapters grouped by topic with research and real-life anecdotes delve into how technological and societal developments have changed the meaning and value of traditional economic data-points, predictive tools, and business concepts. Robert S. Kricheff provides specifics on new and more valuable data sources as well as better methods for applying the information to investing, business, and even your career.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jan 2019) 4aChange management, Investment, Finance, Asset value, Inflation, Fallacies, Globalization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2018z9783110603101oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishz97831106040160 cEPUBz97815474007750 cprintz978154741682040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781547400751423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781547400751.jpg  aPDA5EBK  a978-3-11-060401-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DBVb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aPDA14ALL  aPDA1ALL